on every display.

00:20:07.085 --> 00:20:09.400
IAN NI-LEWIS: That's a good
point because if you've got a

00:20:09.400 --> 00:20:12.620
black line around, that's going
to scale differently,

00:20:12.620 --> 00:20:15.520
and it's going to end up
actually being invisible on

00:20:15.520 --> 00:20:17.150
some devices and too
thick on others.

00:20:17.150 --> 00:20:18.395
DAN GALPIN: Exactly,
and you end up with

00:20:18.395 --> 00:20:19.620
these aliasing artifacts.

00:20:19.620 --> 00:20:22.810
Like, you can see here on the
board on the very, very left,

00:20:22.810 --> 00:20:24.845
