00:32:20.830 --> 00:32:23.690
I think that there's really
an opportunity for--

00:32:23.690 --> 00:32:24.750
IAN NI-LEWIS: Yeah, see, I don't
feel that way because I

00:32:24.750 --> 00:32:25.420
hate other people.

00:32:25.420 --> 00:32:27.630
But touch screen--

00:32:27.630 --> 00:32:30.235
now, that's something
I can get behind.

00:32:30.235 --> 00:32:31.440
DAN GALPIN: I mean, I think,
I would love to see--

00:32:31.440 --> 00:32:34.130
"StarCraft" was a great
single-player experience.

00:32:34.130 --> 00:32:37.405
But as a multi-player
game was where it--

00:32:37.405 --> 00:32:38.590
IAN NI-LEWIS: Yeah,
no question.

00:32:38.590 --> 00:32:43.450
But that doesn't feel
like it's the core

00:32:43.450 --> 00:32:44.350
to the phone, right?

00:32:44.350 --> 00:32:46.640
Or are you just saying that in
general, we're not seeing

00:32:46.640 --> 00:32:48.660
enough multi-player experiences,
even though these

00:32:48.660 --> 00:32:49.230
things are--

00:32:49.230 --> 00:32:50.410
DAN GALPIN: Yeah, even
though these things

00:32:50.410 --> 00:32:51.030
are connected devices.

00:32:51.030 --> 00:32:53.090
Like, I want to see people
do a lot of really cool

00:32:53.090 --> 00:32:53.360
multi-player stuff.

00:32:53.360 --> 00:32:54.810
IAN NI-LEWIS: Well, I mean part
